{"TopicId":174365,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"flat kerbin mod request","CreatedByName":"Hunony","CreatedById":184586,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-28T15:46:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hunony","CreatedById":184586,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-28T15:46:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndude this would be awesome lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-28T17:03:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2153628243\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/167858-flat-kerbin/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3226826\u0026amp;embedComment=3226826\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:280px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4885656734\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/167858-flat-kerbin/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3256668\u0026amp;embedComment=3256668\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:311px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9724459883\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/156657-flat-earth-mod/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2961723\u0026amp;embedComment=2961723\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:311px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9595574727\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/143279-flat-kerbin/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2782924\u0026amp;embedComment=2782924\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:259px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could go on for years, but you\u0027ll get the idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe TLDR is no KSP doesn\u0027t work like that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a well known fact that flat planet threads in general usually get very messy and not a lot to do with the thread subject .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dimas152","CreatedById":179714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T02:28:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ny\u0027 sure? if one appeared it will break the universe\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceMouse","CreatedById":126931,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T05:51:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlol. There\u0027s probably no reason it wouldn\u0027t work in KSP but it would be confined to regular gravity so, going anywhere besides the middle would be like climbing a vertical wall.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be a interesting engineering challenge actually. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T07:44:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could use a height map with a very large deformity and a very small initial radius to make a planet roughly disk shaped, but it wouldn\u0027t work right, and the game would only consider the shpere that the heigh map is overlaid on to have actual mass. The large extensions caused by the heightmap won\u0027t matter for gravity purposes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt wouldn\u0027t work anywhere close to right. Also, I wouldn\u0027t want to make a 2d projection of the surface of Kerbin the way cartographers have done for Earth (like the UN symbol), but if you want it... you do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T10:06:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367586\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525067485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126931\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceMouse\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, SpaceMouse said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be a interesting engineering challenge actually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoding challenge.\u00A0\u00A0 The KSP engine apparently won\u0027t allow disc shaped planets.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCause,\u00A0 physics, ya\u0027know?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T10:28:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin of \u003Cs\u003Einfinite\u003C/s\u003E very long radius is technically flat.\u003Cbr\u003E\nProbably Kopernicus would allow this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdditional idea.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn\u003Cem\u003Eflat\u003C/em\u003Eable Kerbin. Get it from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E and inflate wherever\u00A0you are, instead of return to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-30T10:30:57Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2018 10:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T10:44:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367683\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525084128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerb\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ein of \u003Cs\u003Einfinite\u003C/s\u003E very long radius is technically flat\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadius of a sphere works in all directions, including \u0022up\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T11:20:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367691\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525085057\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadius of a sphere works in all directions, including \u0022up\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, and any place at Kerbin will be flat.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T11:23:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367712\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525087215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, and any place at Kerbin will be flat.\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Kerbin is infinitely big, then for practical purposes, I guess it would be flat.\u00A0\u00A0 But then it would be the size of the entire universe, so there would be no \u0022up\u0022, or space, or anything to do but go \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flatland\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esideways\u003C/a\u003E.....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T11:29:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525087412\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut then it would be the size of the entire universe, so there would be no \u0022up\u0022, or space, or anything to do but go \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flatland\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Esideways\u003C/a\u003E.....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt can be just VERY big, not necessary infinite.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSociety of \u003Cem\u003EAlmost\u003C/em\u003E Flat Earth\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-30T11:30:23Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2018 11:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceMouse","CreatedById":126931,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T16:18:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367671\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525082816\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoding challenge.\u00A0\u00A0 The KSP engine apparently won\u0027t allow disc shaped planets.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCause,\u00A0 physics, ya\u0027know?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou could probably fake it with a very small planet with strong gravity and Konstructs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Andetch","CreatedById":173643,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-17T15:34:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo make this, you would also need to make Kerbin the center of the system and have Kerbol and all the planets go around Kerbin... I wish someone would make the flat Kerbin mod, to the exact specs of flat-tard models just to prove how silly they are..... Then it could change into something actually fun by making it a Discworld mod, put Kerbin on the back of 4 elephants standing on the shell of a giant space turtle - so we can launch missions to find out the turtle\u0027s gender?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-04T12:04:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223367671\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525082816\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/30/2018 at 6:06 AM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoding challenge.\u00A0\u00A0 The KSP engine apparently won\u0027t allow disc shaped planets.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCause,\u00A0 physics, ya\u0027know?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoding challenge accepted .... managed to make a flat asteroid\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for a planet, not so sure that\u0027s gonna go over so well as KSP keeps having a hissy fit ... but oblong asteroids or flat potatoes are totally doable\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/pSiBhKl9NwA?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-04T16:31:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA solution I\u0027d propose (though I\u0027m not a coder nor a developer of any sort, but at least I\u0027m trying), is to create a Kerbal Konstruct Structure, that is a massive plane to the size desired to create a \u0027flat\u0027 world. Then, to get gravity and physics working properly, I would place a massive planet underneath the plane, but size and gravity adjusted to fit the plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough there could be a problem with large KK structures or some other issue I\u0027m not seeing, but it\u0027s an idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll draw up a model later today to help explain what I\u0027m thinking the likely sizes required to make it work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0something0","CreatedById":182790,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T16:36:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is my idea: Basically, you have a really big spherical planet and only a small section of it is Kerbin to give the impression that its flat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}